  "text": "It has been suggested that ICC scores do not take into account the scale of measurement and the size of error that is clinically relevant [CITATION_1] . Therefore, a complementary way of measuring reliability or limit of agreement was also performed using 'Bland-Altman Plots' , where the difference between baseline and final NPRS-NP values (in Y-axis) were plotted against the mean of NPRS-NP scores at baseline and final measurement (in X-axis) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
